From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: GE-Proton <git@localhost>
Date: Thu, 9 Jul 2026 07:45:00 -0600
Subject: [PATCH] winepulse: Do not starve the current hotplug flow.

The DualSense mono speaker ordering fix defers capture-side controller deltas
while a render event is pending, so games see the controller speaker sink before
reacting to microphone/monitor hotplug. However, the generic endpoint delta
worker also yielded the current flow whenever the opposite flow already had
queued additions/removals. With a DualSense reconnect this produced a livelock:
capture waited for render, while render kept yielding to the already queued
capture endpoints.

Only yield to the other flow when the current flow does not have its own pending
event. If render has a sink/card event pending, let render refresh even if
capture endpoints are already queued.
---
 dlls/winepulse.drv/pulse.c | 5 +++--
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/dlls/winepulse.drv/pulse.c b/dlls/winepulse.drv/pulse.c
index 11111111111..22222222222 100644
--- a/dlls/winepulse.drv/pulse.c
+++ b/dlls/winepulse.drv/pulse.c
@@ -651,7 +651,8 @@ static NTSTATUS pulse_get_endpoint_ids(void *args)
         }
         if (!list_count(list_added) && !list_count(list_removed))
         {
-            if (list_count(other_list_added) + list_count(other_list_removed)
-                    || (g_phys_event_mask & other_event_mask))
+            if (!(g_phys_event_mask & event_mask)
+                    && (list_count(other_list_added) + list_count(other_list_removed)
+                    || (g_phys_event_mask & other_event_mask)))
             {
                 params->more_data = TRUE;
